.el .ds Aq '
.TH carbonado 1  "carbonado 2.0.0" 
.SH NAME
carbonado \- Apocalypse\-resistant archival for files and directory trees
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcarbonado\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Encode and decode Carbonado archives for single files or directory trees.
.PP
KEY MATERIAL:
  First encrypted encode auto\-generates a BIP39 mnemonic (24 words), saved in plaintext at the path from `carbonado key path` (override: CARBONADO_MNEMONIC_PATH). Later encode/decode reuse it unless `\-\-master` is given. Decode never auto\-generates.
.PP
ARTIFACTS:
  Single\-file default: inboard headered `{hash}.c{fmt:02x}` (format 14 → `.c0e`).
  `\-\-outboard`: bare main + optional `.out`/`.par` sidecars (single\-file only).
  Directory: inboard Adamantine 1.0 catalog `.adam.c14` (or `.adam.c15` with `\-\-encrypted`) and heterogeneous bare segment mains (c4/c6 or c5/c7). Output defaults to `{input}\-archive/`.
.PP
See `carbonado <command> \-\-help` for per\-command options.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
carbonado\-key(1)
Manage persisted BIP39 seed (plaintext; see `carbonado key path`)
.TP
carbonado\-encode(1)
Encode a file or directory into a Carbonado archive
.TP
carbonado\-decode(1)
Decode a headered archive, bare outboard main, or Adamantine catalog
.TP
carbonado\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH EXTRA
EXAMPLES:
  carbonado encode secret.bin \-\-format 15
  carbonado encode ./my\-project \-\-encrypted \-o ./archive\-out

  carbonado encode myfile.bin \-\-outboard \-\-format 14
  carbonado encode ./my\-project \-o ./archive\-out
  carbonado decode ./archive\-out/<catalog>.adam.c14 \-o ./restored
  carbonado decode ./archive\-out/<catalog>.adam.c15 \-o ./restored

  carbonado key path
  carbonado key show
.SH VERSION
v2.0.0
